ðŸŒ Web query:

```web
vite-plugin-image-optimizer configuration options jpg jpeg supported
```

ðŸ’¡ Result:

Yes â€” vite-plugin-image-optimizer supports JPG/JPEG. It exposes separate jpeg and jpg config keys (and its default file test includes jpe?g), and those keys accept the same options you would pass to Sharp's jpeg() output options. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com), [sharp.pixelplumbing.com](https://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/api-output/?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

Quick details
- Supported by default: files matching /\.(jpe?g|png|gif|tiff|webp|svg|avif)$/i (so .jpg and .jpeg are included). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))  
- Config keys: jpeg and jpg (both present in the plugin defaults). Options you set there are forwarded to Sharp. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))  
- What options you can use: any Sharp jpeg() output options such as quality (1â€“100), progressive, chromaSubsampling (e.g. '4:4:4'), optimiseCoding/optimizeCoding, mozjpeg, trellisQuantisation, overshootDeringing, optimiseScans/optimizeScans, quantisationTable, force, etc. See Sharpâ€™s docs for full list and defaults. ([sharp.pixelplumbing.com](https://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/api-output/?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

Example
- vite.config.ts snippet (illustrative):
  ViteImageOptimizer({
    jpeg: {
      quality: 80,
      progressive: true,
      chromaSubsampling: '4:4:4',
      mozjpeg: true
    },
    jpg: {
      quality: 80
    }
  })

Notes / tips
- If you want different behavior for .jpg vs .jpeg you can set both keys; otherwise setting just jpeg is fine because the pluginâ€™s default test matches both extensions. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))  
- Use mozjpeg for better compression at the cost of slower encoding (Sharp option mozjpeg: true). ([sharp.pixelplumbing.com](https://sharp.pixelplumbing.com/api-output/?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

If you want, I can:
- Give a ready-to-drop vite.config.ts example tuned for web delivery (balancing quality and size), or
- Show how to enable/disable processing for files in your public folder or add caching options.

- exclude â€” string | RegExp | string[]

- include â€” string | RegExp | string[]

- includePublic â€” boolean  
  - Default: true â€” whether to optimize assets inside Viteâ€™s public directory (recursively). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- logStats â€” boolean  
  - Default: true â€” log optimization stats (size delta, percent, savings). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

  - Default: multipass: true, plugins: preset-default (with specific overrides such as keeping viewBox, not minifying IDs, etc.), sortAttrs, and addAttributesToSVGElement to add xmlns. You can pass a custom SVGO config. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- png â€” Sharp PngOptions (object)  
  - Default: { quality: 100 } (Sharp options). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- jpeg / jpg â€” Sharp JpegOptions (object)  
  - Default: { quality: 100 } (Sharp options). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- tiff â€” Sharp TiffOptions (object)  
  - Default: { quality: 100 } (Sharp options). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- gif â€” Sharp GifOptions (object)  
  - Default: {} (gif not losslessly compressed by Sharp). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- webp â€” Sharp WebPOptions (object)  
  - Default: { lossless: true } (Sharp options). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- avif â€” Sharp AvifOptions (object)  
  - Default: { lossless: true } (Sharp options). ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- cache â€” boolean  
  - Default: false â€” whether to cache optimized results. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

- cacheLocation â€” string | undefined  
  - Default: undefined â€” custom cache path when caching is enabled. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/blob/main/README.md?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

Other important notes
- sharp and svgo are not bundled: you must install them yourself as dev dependencies if you want image (sharp) and/or SVG (svgo) optimization. The README warns about this and shows install instructions. ([github.com](https://github.com/FatehAK/vite-plugin-image-optimizer?utm_source=chatgpt.com), [npmjs.com](https://www.npmjs.com/package/vite-plugin-image-optimizer/v/1.0.8?utm_source=chatgpt.com))

Contributors guide: https://github.com/jitsi/jitsi-meet/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md

Closes #16341 

## Summary
This PR introduces an interactive zoom and pan feature for screen shares displayed in the large video view. This enhancement allows users to focus on specific details of a presentation or shared desktop, significantly improving the experience when viewing high-resolution content or small text.

The feature is implemented for both mobile and desktop clients, using intuitive, platform-native controls.


## Key Features
- **Interactive Zoom & Pan:** Users can now dynamically zoom and pan the screen share video
- **Mobile Touch Controls:**

    - Pinch-to-zoom to intuitively control the zoom level.

    - Single-finger drag to pan the view after it has been zoomed.

- **Desktop Mouse Controls:**
     - Mouse wheel scroll to zoom in and out of the content.
     - Click-and-drag with the primary mouse button to pan the view.


## Motivation
When viewing a high-resolution screen share, especially on smaller devices, it can be difficult to read small text or see fine details. Currently, there is no built-in way to magnify the content. This feature directly addresses this usability gap by providing intuitive controls for users to inspect the screen share content more closely, creating a more accessible and effective meeting experience.

  - Updated guidelines to reflect SVG-based annotation tools.
